---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Colophon"
  description="Why this site is called Motif of the Mind: small recurring ideas, varied like jazz. Living documents with a status and a last-updated date, self-hosted, fast, almost no JavaScript."
>
  <article class="container section colophon">
    <header class="colophon__header">
      <h1>Colophon</h1>
      <p class="muted colophon__lede">Why this site, and how it works.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose colophon__body">
      <p>
        The name is <strong>Motif of the Mind</strong>. A motif is a small,
        recurring idea: the atom you build from. State it, turn it over, return
        to it changed; everything here grows from pieces that small.
      </p>
      <p>
        I think about it the way I listen to jazz: a few themes and familiar
        phrases, stated and restated, but the variations never run out. The
        standards stay, the solo is never the same twice. That is what I mean by
        <strong>knowledge as process</strong>: the value is in the takes, not the
        finished score.
      </p>
      <p>
        So nothing here is final. Every post carries a status (
        <code>draft</code>, <code>working</code>, or <code>stable</code>) and a
        last-updated date, so you can tell which takes are still being worked out.
        Drafts stay off the <a href="/writing/">Writing</a> list until they’re
        ready; revising in public is the point, not an embarrassment.
      </p>
      <p>
        The room is kept plain so the playing carries: Swiss-typographic,
        self-hosted
        <a href="https://hanken.co/products/hanken-grotesk" rel="noopener"
          >Hanken Grotesk</a
        >, statically built, with no embeds, no trackers, and almost no
        JavaScript, fast and meant to stay legible for a long time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <style>
    .colophon {
      max-width: 52rem;
    }
    .colophon__header {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }
    .colophon__lede {
      font-size: var(--step-1);
      margin-top: var(--space-s);
    }
    .colophon__body {
      max-width: var(--measure);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
